(secondQuint)Telemedicine Qualifying Transition Between Tertiary and Primary Health Care in Stable Coronary Artery Disease Patients.

 This study is a randomized non-inferiority trial for patients with chronic coronary artery disease from a tertiary hospital with outpatient discharge criteria.

 The purpose is to compare the use of telemedicine in the quality of care transition between tertiary care and primary care patients (intervention group), with patients who remain in the outpatient clinic of a tertiary hospital (control group).

